🛠️ Bookey Project Environment Setup Guide

■Step 1: Terminal Setup and Git Clone in Eclipse
Follow these steps to fetch the source code using the internal terminal in Eclipse.

 1. Open Terminal: Go to Window > Show View > Other... > Terminal.

 2. Launch New Terminal: Click the Open a New Terminal View icon and select Git Bash.

 3. Check Version: Type git --version in the terminal to verify installation.

 4. Change Directory:

  A. Type cd D: and press Enter.

  B. Type cd ./dev/workspace to move to your workspace folder.

 5. Clone Project: Use the URL from the Bookey GitHub repository.

  A. Run: git clone https://github.com/beenjh6088/bookey.git

■Step 2: Project Import and Server Deployment
Import the cloned source into Eclipse and register it with the Tomcat server.

 1. Import Project: Right-click in Project Explorer > Import... > Existing Projects into Workspace and select the bookey folder.

 2. Add to Server: In the Servers tab, right-click on your Tomcat server and select Add and Remove....

 3. Register App: Select bookey from the left list and move it to the right (Configured).

 4. Configure Path: Double-click Tomcat in the Servers tab > Go to the Modules tab at the bottom > Select bookey, click Edit, and change the Path to /.

■Step 3: Database Connection Pool (JNDI) Configuration
Configure the Oracle database connection details for the DAO.

 1. Open Configuration: Open the context.xml file located in the Servers project.

 2. Add Resource: Insert the following snippet inside the <Context> tag:

   <Resource name="jdbc/oracle"
          auth="Container"
          type="javax.sql.DataSource"
          driverClassName="oracle.jdbc.OracleDriver"
          url="jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521:xe"
          username="bookey"
          password="tiger"
          maxActive="20"
          maxIdle="10"
          maxWait="-1"/>

■Setp 4: Syncronize with your git repository
rm -rf ./.git

git init

git config --global user.name Papataya

git config --global user.email beenjh6088@gmail.com

